# =============================================================================
# crontab.example – Cron job template for home-automation-scripts
#
# USAGE:
#   Review this file, then install the entries with the helper tool:
#
#     python3 tools/cron_installer.py install
#
#   Or add them manually:
#
#     crontab -e
#
#   and paste the relevant entries, replacing $REPO_ROOT and $PYTHON with
#   the correct absolute paths for your machine.
#
# VARIABLE SUBSTITUTION (tools/cron_installer.py replaces these automatically):
#   $REPO_ROOT  – absolute path to the cloned repository root
#   $PYTHON     – path to the Python interpreter (.venv/bin/python3 when present,
#                 otherwise the python3 that invoked the installer)
#
# CRON SYNTAX REFERENCE:
#   ┌─────────── minute         (0–59)
#   │ ┌───────── hour           (0–23)
#   │ │ ┌─────── day of month   (1–31)
#   │ │ │ ┌───── month          (1–12)
#   │ │ │ │ ┌─── day of week    (0–7, 0 and 7 are both Sunday)
#   │ │ │ │ │
#   * * * * *  command to run
#
# SAFETY TIPS:
#   - Always use absolute paths; cron runs with a minimal PATH.
#   - Redirect stdout and stderr to a log file so failures remain visible:
#       >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/cron.log 2>&1
#   - Avoid embedding secrets in cron entries; use the .env file instead.
#   - Set MAILTO="" at the top of your crontab to suppress email on each run.
#
# See docs/cron_jobs.md for the full scheduling guide.
# =============================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cron environment (uncomment and adjust as needed)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MAILTO=""
# SHELL=/bin/bash

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Task runner – daily maintenance
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Run the backup task every day at 02:00.
0 2 * * * $PYTHON $REPO_ROOT/tools/runner.py run backup >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Run the health-check task every 15 minutes.
*/15 * * * * $PYTHON $REPO_ROOT/tools/runner.py run health_check >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# Run all registered tasks once a week on Sunday at 03:00.
# Replace task names with the actual task names from `runner.py list`.
# 0 3 * * 0 $PYTHON $REPO_ROOT/tools/runner.py run task1 task2 >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Startup tasks
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Validate required environment variables at every system boot.
@reboot $PYTHON $REPO_ROOT/tools/env_loader.py >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/env_check.log 2>&1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Strava sync – fetch recent activities once per day at 06:00.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Run via the automation CLI (recommended):
0 6 * * * $PYTHON $REPO_ROOT/tools/automation.py run strava-sync >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/strava.log 2>&1

# Alternatively, run via the bash wrapper (logs timestamp prefix from the shell):
# 0 6 * * * /usr/bin/env bash -c 'cd $REPO_ROOT && ./run_strava_sync.sh >> $REPO_ROOT/logs/strava.log 2>&1'
